data.text:
Observable Universe → Pisces-Cetus Supercluster Complex → Laneakea Supercluster

The Local Group is the galaxy group in which the Milky Way is located. It contains the following galaxies:

Milky Way (barred spiral galaxy)

Large Magellanic Cloud (irregular spiral galaxy)

Small Magellanic Cloud (irregular galaxy)

NGC 6822 (irregular galaxy)

IC 1613 (irregular galaxy)

Andromeda Galaxy (barred spiral galaxy)

Triangulum Galaxy (loose spiral galaxy)

WLM (irregular galaxy)

NGC 3109 (irregular galaxy)

Sagittarius Dwarf (dwarf spherical galaxy)
